# Allowlist style: ignore EVERYTHING, then re-include only the committed
# scaffold. This is airtight by construction — any file Hermes writes into the
# checkout (the .hermes-home/ runtime dir, SEO research output you generate
# while testing, future Hermes artifacts we've never heard of) is ignored by
# default, so secrets and session data can never be committed by a stray
# `git add -A`.
/*

# Re-include the committed scaffold (and nothing else).
!/seo-skills/
!/.envrc
!/config.yaml
!/SOUL.md
!/README.md
!/LICENSE
!/.gitignore
